                            <comment id="12412409" author="anurag" created="Fri, 19 May 2006 03:53:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like It has got some conflict with one of the recent commits.&lt;br/&gt;
I will reupload it after fixing the conflict and fixing the mistake Olav pointed out&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12412639" author="anurag" created="Sat, 20 May 2006 22:55:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed resolve conflict.&lt;br/&gt;
added notifyException in createSQLXML&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12412820" author="rhillegas" created="Tue, 23 May 2006 03:41:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. JDBC4 tests run cleanly. At first derbyall choked on the nist tests, due to the outstanding bug which breaks those tests. I removed the nist suite from the tests and re-ran. Derbyall then passed cleanly except for the wisconsin diffs and a failure in the unit suite. I re-ran the unit suite, which then passed. Committed at subversion revision 408733.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12412873" author="narayanan" created="Tue, 23 May 2006 14:47:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Assigned it to me by mistake! This patch is committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12412988" author="djd" created="Wed, 24 May 2006 04:43:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the property  junit.xa.single should have a prefix of derbyTesting. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Junit should be reserved for code associated with the junit harness itself, not derby&apos;s tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12413097" author="anurag" created="Wed, 24 May 2006 17:23:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;changed junit.xa.single to derbyTesting.xa.single&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12413283" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 26 May 2006 02:13:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;JDBC4 tests pass cleanly. Derbyall passes modulo wisconsin diffs. Committed derby-1214_3.diff at subversion revision 409420.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
